This paper discusses the use of observability Gramian for partially observed robotic path planning problems, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses optimization measures, which can be related to optimization algorithms used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper may involve computer vision techniques for observation uncertainty (cs.CV) and system control theory for observability (cs.SY).
